5/ This is the first time I am speaking about politics and war on Twitter. Wish I was tweeting about NFTs instead.

If you can support Ukraine in any way, such as donating to the charity, or a humanitarian group - please do.

And let's hope this nightmare will be over soon.

4/ Most Russian people don't want this war. My dad lives in Russia. Lots of Russian people have relatives in Ukraine.

This is about politics, the people are against the conflict. Nobody wants a bloodshed.

3/ Nobody wants a war with Russia. This is what happened in 2014 when I was there. And this is what will likely happen now. The country is pretty much on its own.

European NATO countries will protect their own borders, of course.

2/ Unfortunately, the predictions are looking dire. As someone who lived in Ukraine most of my life here's what I think can happen.

Since Ukraine is not in NATO, US or European forces won't intervene.
